text:
The positive features of The French Quarters: 
1) Great location on Restaurant Row...East of Time Square...with Theaters to the North, South, and East; 
2) We were treated politely and professionally by all of the staff; 
3) A very nice clean room with plenty of space for a six-night stay; and 
4) A great bathroom and shower...with plenty of hot water. 

The negative features of the French Quarters: 
1) Almost impossible to sleep between 3:00 AM to 5:00 AM because of street noise...mostly people walking down the street yelling and cursing at each other...but also there is garbage truck pick-up every night during that same time...and construction noise too; 
2) There is a kitchenette but no dishes or silverware so you need to buy or bring your own...also there is a mini refrigerator but no microwave...so we ate all of our leftovers cold; 
3) Award for the worlds thinnest bathroom tissue...we had to go to Walgreens and buy a six-pack of bathroom tissue for the week; and 
4) The breakfast was inconsistent in that if you arrive early the selection was good but never replaced...basically any pastries not served first thing in the morning were saved for staff...the milk and orange juice were only replaced once during breakfast in our six day stay...eggs were only served twice during our six day stay which is unbelievable since there is a kitchen downstairs...the dirty dishes were not removed from the tables before the end of breakfast leaving limited places to sit...and the tables were never wiped clean and I saw the same breakfast food stains on a table three days in a row...so my wife only went to breakfast twice during our six day stay...but I have to eat breakfast every morning...so we would stop and eat breakfast at any of the breakfast restaurants in the neighborhood. 

Conclusion: This could be a great hotel if the owners and staff cared about the details. 

Lessons Learned: I will never stay in New York City in any hotel less that ten-stories so I can get a full night sleep...and next time I will book a New York City hotel without a breakfast but with a mini refrigerator and microwave.
